# Do NOT auto-install peerDependencies on `npm install`.
#
# WHY: npm v7+ installs peerDependencies automatically. Our single peer is
# `openclaw` itself — the host runtime that loads this plugin. If npm pulls it
# into node_modules/openclaw, `openclaw plugins install .` then trips over a
# bundled copy of the very runtime it is installing into (arc hit this live on
# the Mac mini — TASK-...-install-f0e6511a). The openclaw runtime is provided by
# the host at load time, never bundled. `omit=peer` keeps node_modules free of it.
#
# tsc still compiles without the real `openclaw` present because src/openclaw-sdk.d.ts
# supplies an ambient declaration for the `openclaw/*` subpath we import.
omit=peer
